So what was your other question?

00:46:39.500 --> 00:46:41.716
It was-- oh, reception in Asia.

00:46:45.050 --> 00:46:48.855
I think that there's-- there's
so much interest in the fish

00:46:48.855 --> 00:46:55.094
that, so far, people seem
pretty excited about the book.

00:46:55.094 --> 00:46:56.510
It's really different
from-- there

00:46:56.510 --> 00:46:59.110
are a lot of arowana
books that exist.

00:46:59.110 --> 00:47:00.596
But they're all like fish care.

00:47:00.596 --> 00:47:02.470
So a lot of times people
will think that I've

00:47:02.470 --> 00:47:05.790
written a fish care book.

00:47:05.790 --> 00:47:09.410
I think I am, right now,
number one in fish and aquarium

00:47:09.410 --> 00:47:10.390
care on Amazon.

00:47:13.150 --> 00:47:15.270
I don't mean to boast.

00:47:18.350 --> 00:47:22.230
I think we'll have to see
what people think of it.

00:47:22.230 --> 00:47:24.290
But I think that they'll
probably be interested

00:47:24.290 --> 00:47:28.380
because it's-- the thing about
the aquarium hobby is that

00:47:28.380 --> 00:47:33.330
there's something so admirable
about it because these people

00:47:33.330 --> 00:47:35.600
know the names of things.

00:47:35.600 --> 00:47:39.710
They know the names of species
that-- the scientific names

00:47:39.710 --> 00:47:43.900
of species that most
of us have no idea,

00:47:43.900 --> 00:47:47.210
and how they fit together
in terms of the evolution,

00:47:47.210 --> 00:47:49.110
and where they're
from, and so forth.

00:47:49.110 --> 00:47:52.210
And they're really interested
in the natural world

00:47:52.210 --> 00:47:53.750
and, and in the
wild, and holding

00:47:53.750 --> 00:47:54.791
onto a piece of the wild.

00:47:54.791 --> 00:47:56.870
I think that's what
attracts people

00:47:56.870 --> 00:48:01.301
to it as much as the looking
like a dragon and the good luck

00:48:01.301 --> 00:48:01.800
stuff.

00:48:01.800 --> 00:48:04.310
I think it's also a
deeper kind of desire

00:48:04.310 --> 00:48:05.612
to connect with nature.

00:48:08.590 --> 00:48:09.090
So, yeah.

00:48:09.090 --> 00:48:10.464
I wouldn't be
surprised if people

00:48:10.464 --> 00:48:14.540
are very interested in
exploring the history of that.

